# Claude Code agent worktrees — transient per-agent git worktrees live here.
# This targeted rule ignores stray non-worktree content under the subtree so
# it never lands in a commit. (Registered worktrees themselves are managed via
# `git worktree remove`/`prune`, not gitignore — git handles those specially.)
# Already-tracked .claude/ files (settings.local.json, agents/*.md, etc.) are
# unaffected — git does not un-track indexed files on a new ignore rule.
.claude/worktrees/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BRP solo-track workspace exception (broadened across two repair commits).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Multiple repo-root .gitignore rules silently match paths inside the BRP
# renderer workspace, dropping tracked source from atomic commits:
#
#   1. 'MANIFEST' — Python sdist artifact filter. On Windows
#      (core.ignorecase=true) this matches solo/brp-renderer/src/manifest/
#      and silently dropped three files from commit 8da89b59. Caught and
#      repaired with a narrow exception in commit fc89ae85.
#
#   2. '*.session.json' — calibration session-data filter. Matches
#      solo/brp-renderer/src/mocks/fixtures/enrollment.session.json and
#      would have silently dropped it from commit 4c. Caught at 4c Hold-2
#      by `git check-ignore -v` enforcement (added to the Hold-2 invariant
#      after the fc89ae85 lesson).
#
# Per-rule narrow exceptions are error-prone — every new repo-root rule
# becomes a new audit point. Broadening to the whole BRP workspace kills
# the entire class of silent-skip drift. The workspace's own
# solo/brp-renderer/.gitignore (committed in 8da89b59) handles its own
# exclusions for node_modules / dist / coverage / *.tsbuildinfo within
# the workspace.
#
# IMPORTANT: this exception MUST be the last-matching rule for any path
# under solo/brp-renderer/. gitignore precedence is last-match-wins; if a
# new exclusion pattern is added below this block it will silently
# re-shadow the BRP workspace. New patterns belong above this block.
!solo/brp-renderer/
!solo/brp-renderer/**

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BRP renderer vendored copy at frontend/src/brp/ — third recurrence repair.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Per OPEN_QUESTIONS.md OQ-7 (post-milestone incorporation), the BRP solo-track
# artifact is also vendored into frontend/src/brp/ as a 4th additive view in
# the existing frontend workspace. The previous repair (commit 3dda7ae6) added
# !solo/brp-renderer/** as a workspace-wide exception, which protected the solo
# workspace cleanly. It did NOT anticipate vendoring into a NEW workspace.
#
# Caught at incorporation commit β's Hold-2 check-ignore enforcement:
# `*.session.json` (line 73) matched
# frontend/src/brp/mocks/fixtures/enrollment.session.json — same exact rule that
# bit at 4c, just at a new location. Same single-concern repair shape as
# fc89ae85 + 3dda7ae6: append a workspace-scoped exception at end-of-file.
#
# GENERALIZED LESSON (third repair, recorded in commit message):
#   Workspace-wide exceptions protect named workspaces, not file classes.
#   Each new vendored location requires its own exception. Future vendoring
#   of BRP code (or any solo-track artifact) into a new workspace MUST be
#   preceded by a .gitignore exception for that location, validated by
#   `git check-ignore -v` against every vendored path.
#
# Same precedence rule applies: this exception MUST stay at end-of-file
# (last-match-wins). New exclusion patterns belong above the BRP exception
# blocks, not below them.
!frontend/src/brp/
!frontend/src/brp/**

